BODY RINGS (
Fig. 3F
). Entire metazonal area with longitudinal striations. Metazonal setae short, length of midbody setae ca 5% of vertical diameter of rings.

TELSON (
Fig. 3E
). Epiproct variable, with an almost absent to short and blunt preanal process. Paraprocts rounded, setose. Hypoproct without any modifications.

PENES (
Fig. 4G
). In form of a short trapezoid, apically with two small subtriangular lobes.
